author: newsroom@capegazette.com (Dave Frederick )
title: Sussex Tech cross country wins boys' and girls' home quad meet
text:
Sussex Tech cross country wins boys' and girls' home quad meet Cape Henlopen runs the table at Lake Forest By Dave Frederick | Oct 15, 2015 Photo by: Dave Frederick Roxy Ramirez of Sussex Tech takes off toward a new school record. 
A beautiful Wednesday afternoon for running at Sussex Tech on the south side of Route 9 was a showcase for the Ravens boys' cross country team, which remained undefeated with wins over Dover 23-34, Smyrna 23-38, and Delmar 15-48. 
Sussex Tech put its first five runners in the top 10 of the race, including Ben Bamforth, second in 16:41; Ian Carlisle, fourth in 17:03; Jairus Hinds, fifth in 17:11; Graham Spellman, ninth in 17:58 and Connor Morrow, 10th in 18:00. 
“Everyone ran really well," said Sussex Tech coach Lou Niccoletti. “We have some tough meets coming up, including Caesar Rodney at home Oct. 28.” 
Oluwafikunayomi Ibironke of Smyrna ran his best time of the season by 20 seconds to win individual honors with a time of 16:28. 
Dover had Sean Sexton finish third in 16:56, with Nyjal Drayton sixth, 17:17; and Adam Spencer eighth, 17:58. Adam Bailey of Smyrna was seventh in 17:19. 
The Sussex Tech girls also got out the broom to sweep past Smyrna 23-38, Dover 18-45 and Delmar 15-46. 
Roxy Ramirez set a school record running 18:54 to place first overall. The Ravens also placed Lakendra Harpe fourth in 22:03, Regan Banning sixth in 22:21, Alexis Singh seventh in 22:26 and Chloe Fisher eighth in 22:29. 
The Cape Henlopen boys picked up three wins in a quad meet at Lake Forest Oct. 14. The Vikings defeated Lake Forest 21-40, Sussex Central 25-34 and Seaford 15-50. 
Cape's top runners were Sam Nye, second in 17:49; Greg Boyce, fifth in 18:34; Lance White, sixth in 18:48; Ricky Brokaw, eighth in 19:08; and Agnstur Nsiah, 10th in 19:16. Overall winner was Drew Harris of Lake Forest in 17:18. 
The Cape girls also added three wins to their season, beating Lake Forest 26-30, Seaford 15-50 and Sussex Central 15-50. 
Cape's top finishers were Sarah Dziak, first in 21:27; Zoey Callard, third in 22:08; Grace Brokaw, fifth in 22:45; Yesenia Ramirez, sixth in 23:12; and Lizzie Finnegan, 11th in 24:41. Delmar is a new player in the sport of cross country. (Photo by: Dave Frederick ) Lane Landis of Sussex Tech. (Photo by: Dave Frederick ) Roxy Ramirez powers to a new school record of 18:54.
